fields.name: AgentConfiguration
fields.description: The machine configuration of the run agent.

fields.name: Arguments
fields.description: The collection of override arguments to be used when executing the run.

fields.name: Credentials
fields.description: The properties that describes a set of credentials that will be used when this run is invoked.

fields.name: DockerFilePath
fields.description: The Docker file path relative to the source location.

fields.name: ImageNames
fields.description: The fully qualified image names including the repository and tag.

fields.name: IsPushEnabled
fields.description: The value of this property indicates whether the image built should be pushed to the registry or not.

fields.name: NoCache
fields.description: The value of this property indicates whether the image cache is enabled or not.

fields.name: Platform
fields.description: The platform properties against which the run has to happen.

fields.name: SourceLocation
fields.description:
The URL(absolute or relative) of the source context. It can be an URL to a tar or git repository.
If it is relative URL, the relative path should be obtained from calling listBuildSourceUploadUrl API.

fields.name: Target
fields.description: The name of the target build stage for the docker build.
